sequenceDiagram
    %% Event Flow — Worked Example (Sequence Diagram)
    %% Source of truth for this diagram: docs/design/event-flow.md
    %% Referenced (linked, not embedded) from: docs/design/event-flow.md
    %% SCOPE: illustrates the M-001 / evt_temp_001 example from event-flow.md
    %% section 3 only (the WARNING-triggering case), not the contrast cases.
    %% Authoritative rules live in event-schema.md, machine-schema.md, api.md —
    %% see event-flow.md section 6 for the full cross-reference table.
    %% VERSIONING: update in place; do not fork per phase (see architecture.mmd).
    actor Operator
    participant Dashboard
    participant API as API Layer
    participant Kafka
    participant EventSvc as Event Service
    participant MachineSvc as Machine Service
    participant AlertSvc as Alert Service
    participant InsightSvc as Insight Service
    participant LLM

    Operator->>Dashboard: Trigger TEMPERATURE_REPORTED (M-001, 95C)
    Dashboard->>API: POST /simulator/events (evt_temp_001)
    API->>API: Validate envelope & payload (event-schema.md §9)
    API->>Kafka: Publish to machine.events (key=M-001)
    API-->>Dashboard: 202 Accepted {eventId, status: PUBLISHED}

    Note over Kafka,AlertSvc: Consumers process independently in parallel — none waits for another

    par Event Service
        Kafka->>EventSvc: deliver evt_temp_001
        EventSvc->>EventSvc: store immutable copy in machine_events
    and Machine Service
        Kafka->>MachineSvc: deliver evt_temp_001
        MachineSvc->>MachineSvc: 95 > threshold(80) -> status WARNING, healthScore 88-10=78
    and Alert Service
        Kafka->>AlertSvc: deliver evt_temp_001
        AlertSvc->>AlertSvc: create alert_001 (severity WARNING)
    end

    Note over Dashboard,API: Eventual consistency window — a GET here could still return pre-event state (architecture.md §15)

    Dashboard->>API: GET /machines/M-001 (poll)
    API-->>Dashboard: machines doc (status: WARNING, healthScore: 78)

    Operator->>Dashboard: Request AI summary
    Dashboard->>API: POST /machines/M-001/summary
    API->>InsightSvc: gather context (evt_prod_098, evt_temp_001, alert_001, machine state)
    InsightSvc->>LLM: call LLM API
    LLM-->>InsightSvc: summary text + recommended actions
    InsightSvc-->>API: summary_001
    API-->>Dashboard: 200 OK summary_001
